  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is and why do hotels have a rack rate?",
  "response": "A rack rate is the standard or published rate for a hotel room, before any discounts or special offers are applied. It is the highest price a hotel charges for a room, and serves as the starting point for all other pricing decisions.\n\nHotels have rack rates for several reasons:\n\n1. **Revenue management:** Rack rates provide a baseline from which hotels can offer discounts and promotions. By starting with a higher rate, hotels can strategically adjust prices to maximize occupancy and revenue based on demand, seasonality, and other factors.\n\n2. **Perceived value:** A high rack rate can create a perception of quality and luxury, which may attract certain types of guests. It also allows the hotel to offer the appearance of a good deal when discounts are applied, making guests feel like they are getting a bargain.\n\n3. **Pricing transparency:** Rack rates provide a clear and consistent starting point for all guests, ensuring that everyone is aware of the maximum price they may have to pay for a room. This transparency can help build trust with customers.\n\n4. **Negotiation tool:** Rack rates give hotels a strong position when negotiating rates with corporate clients, travel agencies, or other large groups. The hotel can offer discounted rates while still maintaining the appearance of providing a special deal.\n\n5. **Yield management:** By having a rack rate, hotels can better manage their inventory and yield. They can adjust prices dynamically based on demand, ensuring they maximize revenue during peak periods and maintain occupancy during slower times.\n\nIn summary, rack rates are an essential tool for hotels to manage their pricing strategies, maintain a perception of value, and optimize revenue and occupancy.",
